From: Sonny Jiang <sonny.jiang@amd.com>
Date: Tue, 23 Jun 2015 11:59:55 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 289/401] drm/amdgpu: reset wprt at cp compute resume
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

This patch is to resolve compute hang at resume time.

Signed-off-by: Sonny Jiang <sonny.jiang@amd.com>
Reviewed-by: Christian KÃ¶nig <christian.koenig@amd.com>
Signed-off-by: Sanjay R Mehta <sanju.mehta@amd.com>
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/gfx_v8_0.c | 4 ++++
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/gfx_v8_0.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/gfx_v8_0.c
index 14242bd..b5cc9e4 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/gfx_v8_0.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/gfx_v8_0.c
@@ -3115,6 +3115,10 @@ static int gfx_v8_0_cp_compute_resume(struct amdgpu_device *adev)
 
 		amdgpu_bo_kunmap(ring->mqd_obj);
 		amdgpu_bo_unreserve(ring->mqd_obj);
+
+		/* reset wptr */
+		ring->wptr = 0;
+		amdgpu_ring_set_wptr(ring);
 	}
 
 	if (use_doorbell) {
